answers.answer: No not normal call your ob..could be a sign of preeclampsia

Its is normal,the lining or "film" so to speak that protects your lins,thickens while your pregnant and can cause blurry vision.I dont remember the term my docter used for it,but i already wear glasses and my eyes seemed to have gotten worse when i was in my first trimester.Its normal but temporary shouldn't be perminent.

Same thing happened to me. Could be a sign of gestational diabetes . My sugar was low that day so I got a migraine with blurred vision. I don't have diabetes but eating regularly and healthy seemed to have help. And getting more sleep and napping when I can

It could be one of three thing like the other girls said... could be your sugar, or blood pressure... or could just be the pregnancy and extra blood flow etc. I would deff call your doc and let them check you out before making any assumptions otherwise.
Pregnancy causes changes in vision. I had to get new contacts.  I'll probably have to get new ones again after baby is born.
I Had A Minor Black Two Days Ago It's Because Of Dehydration And I Was Lacking Vitamin B, It Is Not Normal. You Should Talk To Your Ob And See What's Going On.

Make sure you tell your Dr. whenever I went to appointments they asked me if I had blurred vision because something could be wrong I can't remember exactly what it was that she told me but she did make sure to ask me when I came in and I do wear glasses.
